Attributions

- The `orchestration/cn-plugin/` plugin architecture (commands, agents,
  skills, companion scripts) is derived from and inspired by
  openai/codex-plugin-cc (https://github.com/openai/codex-plugin-cc),
  the Codex plugin for Claude Code by OpenAI, licensed under Apache-2.0.

- The Phase 5 "Review-Fix Loop" design in `orchestration/fuguectl/SKILL.md`
  draws on published work on agentic verification loops:
    - Tim Williams, "LLM Verification Loops: Best Practices and Patterns"
    - "Loop Engineering: Why the Best AI Agents in 2026 Are Built as Loops"
    - Reflexion / Self-Refine (academic literature)

- The `Workspace isolation` and `Experience memory` concepts in
  `orchestration/fuguectl/` are inspired by Zleap-AI/Zleap-Agent
  (https://github.com/Zleap-AI/Zleap-Agent) — concepts only; the code is
  an independent implementation, as Zleap ships without a license.

- The provider-runtime bridge was informed by SeemSeam/claude_codex_bridge
  (https://github.com/SeemSeam/claude_codex_bridge) as a reference system;
  Fugunano's public runtime surface and implementation naming are independent.

- `fugue self-harness` is an independent engine-native abstraction of
  Shanghai Artificial Intelligence Laboratory's paper "Self-Harness:
  Harnesses That Improve Themselves" (arXiv:2606.09498), by Hangfan Zhang,
  Shao Zhang, Kangcong Li, Chen Zhang, Yang Chen, Yiqun Zhang, Lei Bai, and
  Shuyue Hu. The implementation here uses the paper's loop shape and
  terminology as a research reference; it does not include paper code.

- The loop's auto-fix vs ask-user finding split, the `fuguectl run` state
  facade, and the `check-docs` docs-match-code drift gate are inspired by
  kunchenguid/no-mistakes (https://github.com/kunchenguid/no-mistakes) and
  lavish-axi (https://github.com/kunchenguid/lavish-axi), licensed MIT —
  ideas only; the implementations here are independent.

- The orchestrator-side ownership / violation-detection idea behind
  `fuguectl integrate --ownership` is inspired by merkyor/Lynn
  (https://gitee.com/merkyor/Lynn).

- `fuguectl skills forge` delegates skill authoring to Anthropic's official
  `skill-creator` Claude Code meta-skill, and the `fuguectl skills validate`
  gate mirrors the checks in its `quick_validate.py`.

- The adaptive router (`fuguectl allocate`) draws on the multi-armed-bandit
  literature: Thompson Sampling (Agrawal & Goyal, 2012) and
  non-stationary / discounted bandits (Garivier & Moulines, 2011).

- The project is named after and conceptually framed by Sakana AI's Fugu
  (https://sakana.ai/fugu/) — many agents behind one interface with a
  learned coordinator (TRINITY) and natural-language orchestration
  (Conductor). Fugunano is an independent, training-free,
  harness-engineered analogue inspired by that framing; it does not derive
  from or include any Sakana AI code.
